{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, bills often do not include the colloquial terms commonly used to describe them.",
    "For example, the \"STOP School Violence Act of 2018\" may be informally described as expanding access to guns in schools, even though the bill itself does not use this phrasing.",
    "Because of these challenges, keyword-based search is insufficient for accurate evidence retrieval.",
    "To address this, we employ an asymmetric semantic similarity model, as described in Section 5.4, enabling us to identify bills that are semantically similar to the Issue FE, even when the style of language used in the claim and the bill differs significantly.",
    "Verifying alignment of claim to bill."
  ]
}